The paper focuses on studying the network characteristics of video streaming services, which involves analyzing the traffic patterns and identifying different streaming strategies. This falls under the scope of computer networks (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also presents an analytical model to study the potential impact of these streaming strategies, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI) or cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of different containers for video streaming, which could be related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
